DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260528T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260528T133000
SUMMARY:Centralized Data Lakes in the Cloud: Scalable and Governed Archite
 ctures
DESCRIPTION:Cloud Data Driven\nGlobal data creation is projected to reach 
 175 zettabytes\, with enterprises managing the majority of this growth. In
  data-intensive industries\, organizations process an average of 9.1 petab
 ytes per enterprise\, exposing the limitations of traditional data warehou
 ses. Yet 76% of organizations struggle with data lake governance\, and 68%
  lack clear data ownership.\n\nThis session presents a research-backed fra
 mework for building centralized\, cloud-based data lakes that deliver meas
 urable improvements in performance\, cost\, and governance. Mature impleme
 ntations achieve 3.2× faster time-to-insight\, 54% reduction in data prep
 aration effort\, and 59.3% lower storage costs. Multi-layered architecture
 s improve query performance by 73%\, increase resource utilization by 81%\
 , and reduce bottlenecks by 67.4%.\n\nCloud-native distributed storage sup
 ports 3.2× higher performance for mixed workloads\, enables 8.7× more co
 ncurrent users\, and delivers 99.99% availability. Beyond architecture\, s
 trong governance and master data management reduce inconsistencies by 83.6
 %\, increase data utilization by 412%\, and improve decision-making speed 
 by 47.2%.\n\nSecurity-by-design approaches reduce unauthorized access by 7
 8.4%\, lower breach likelihood by 56.2%\, and decrease compliance penaltie
 s by 85.4%.\n\nAttendees will gain practical\, data-driven strategies to d
 esign scalable\, secure\, and governance-centric cloud data lakes.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/cloud-data-driven/events/314133608/
